# ConstructQA Agent — Core Rules

## Product

AI test automation for **OpenProject-style construction workflows**. Stack: Next.js 16 App Router, Clerk auth, Groq (`llama-3.1-8b-instant`), custom CSS in `app/globals.css` (no Tailwind in components).

## Before coding Next.js

Read guides under `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` — this project uses **Next.js 16** with breaking API differences from older versions.

## File placement

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Routes & pages | `app/` |
| Shared UI | `app/components/` |
| API routes | `app/api/` |
| Business logic | `lib/` |
| Scripts | `scripts/` |
| Docs | `docs/` |
| Samples / tests | `samples/`, `tests/` |

Use `@/` imports (maps to repo root).

## Do not

- Commit secrets (`.env.local`, keys). Only `.env.example` is tracked.
- Add `framer-motion` or tags like `motion.div` — not a dependency; causes parse errors.
- Create duplicate nested project folders.
- Expand scope beyond the user request.

## Verify before PR

```bash
npm run build
npm run lint
npm run test:validate
```

See `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md` and `AGENTS.md`.
